ce:section.ce:para:
In the present study, the as-prepared CDs were spherical with sizes of 5–8 nm characterized by TEM and DLS analysis (Fig. S1). The CDs featured an absorption peak at 450 nm and an emission peak at 640 nm (Fig. S2). Further, the CDs were encapsulated into liposomes to prepare CDs liposomes using the thin film hydration method [29], and the morphology of CDs liposomes was investigated by cryo-TEM (Fig. 1
                        ). After loading CDs, it was observed that each liposome was filled with CDs (Fig. 1b), although their size (60–80 nm) and morphology (spherical shape) had not changed basically (Fig. 1a vs b). Further investigation demonstrated that compared with pure CDs, CDs liposomes had an obvious PL change. Specifically, as shown in Fig. 2
                        a, a non-negligible change in the color under UV light irradiation (254 nm and 365 nm) was observed. In addition, the absorption peak of CDs liposomes at 440 nm was weakened (Fig. 2b). More importantly, compared with the PL spectrum of pure CDs, the PL intensity of CDs liposomes was significantly increased (5-fold enhancement) with an obvious blue shift of about 10 nm (Fig. 2c). It was reported that the encapsulation of CDs into liposomes would lead to a slightly weaker absorption peak [29], and our data were consistent with this phenomenon. Furthermore, in our present study, enhanced PL emissions of CDs were observed when CDs were encapsulated into liposomes, which has been reported rarely so far.
